# ============================================================
# Keystatic CMS — Shared Password Access
# ============================================================
# Keystatic saves blog posts directly to the server filesystem (content/blog/).
# Access to /keystatic is protected by a shared password — no GitHub account needed.
#
# Setup (one-time):
#   1. Choose a strong password and set KEYSTATIC_PASSWORD below
#   2. Generate KEYSTATIC_SECRET with: openssl rand -hex 32
#   3. Add both to Hostinger hPanel → Websites → Manage → Environment Variables
#   4. Share the password with your marketing team
#
# Workflow for marketing team:
#   - Go to https://mamafern.com/keystatic
#   - Enter the shared password (stored as a 30-day cookie)
#   - Create/edit posts — they save immediately to the server
#
# To version-control posts after editing (run on server):
#   git add content/blog/ && git commit -m "content: new posts" && git push
KEYSTATIC_PASSWORD=
KEYSTATIC_SECRET=

# ============================================================
# Hosting — Hostinger Node.js
# ============================================================
PORT=3000
NODE_ENV=production
